03/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The European Commission's (EC) director for the Western Balkans, Reinhard Priebe, reiterated on Wednesday (2 March) that the EU expects fair and democratic local elections on 13 March. 
He was in Skopje to launch the EC's process of monitoring reforms in the country. 
Macedonia applied for official EU candidate member status last month. 
Priebe described the upcoming municipal vote as the first serious test of Macedonia's institutions. 
(A1 TV - 02/03/05)
